Most athletes are having physical trainings well based on academic findings in the field of sports sciences, and making efforts to effectively improve their sports performance. However, sports sciences are not only for athletes. Understanding sports sciences would be valuable for everyone to consider the ways for living a long and healthy life. In this course, we are aiming to understand the basis of our body and movements, and reconsider our own health, by learning sports sciences.

In this course, in addition to auditing the lecture, you will be required to discuss about some topics, conduct measurements of some body structures and functions, and do some exercises outside the room or at the gymnasium. Thus, you may be asked to bring cloths and shoes suitable for exercise in some lessons. 
